By Kingsley Nwezeh Governor Yayaha Bello of Kogi State and his wife, Rasheedat Bello; Minister of Women Affairs, Pauline Tallen; Chairmen of Senate and House Committees on Air Force, Senator Bala Ibn Na’alla and Hon Shehu Koku; service chiefs led by the Chief of Defence Staff, General Abayomi Olonisakin; Chief of Air Staff, Air Marshal Sadique Abubakar are among the dignitaries attending the burial of Flying Officer Tolulope Arotile, who died in Kaduna.
The fallen officer is being accorded full military honours at the National Military Cemetery located at the Airport Road, Abuja as the burial gets underway.
Military burial ceremony leading to her interment is in progress.   Details later….